<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API error rates>
We are investigating increased errors when making changes to some hosted zones, and creation of new hosted zones using the Route 53 API. DNS queries are not affected by this issue, which are all being answered as normal.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API error rates>
We are continuing to investigate elevated API errors when making changes to some hosted zones, and creation of new hosted zones using the Route 53 API. DNS queries are not affected by this issue, which are all being answered normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: [RESOLVED] Increased API error rates>
We have identified root cause and are working towards recovery of elevated error rates using the Route 53 API. DNS queries are not affected by this issue, which are all being answered normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased API error rates>
Between 9:25 AM and 11:30 AM PDT, we experienced increased errors when making changes to some hosted zones, and creating new hosted zones using the Route 53 API and Console. The issue has been recovered, and all services are operating normally. DNS queries were not affected by this issue, which were all answered normally.
